Do the following in SBCL:

;(load "/path/to/asdf.lisp")
;(load "/path/to/slime/swank.asd")
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op :swank)
(sb-ext:save-lisp-and-die "sbclswank" :executable t) 
                ; :toplevel #'swank:create-server)

Then run ./sbclswank --eval '(swank:create-server)' .

Then connect from SLIME or SLIMV.

Check out how to do in CLISP using:

;(load "/path/to/asdf.lisp")
;(load "/path/to/slime/swank.asd")
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op :swank)
(ext:saveinitmem "clispswank" :quiet t :norc t :executable t)
                ; :init-function #'swank:create-server)
                
To use gambol API for prolog:
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op :gambol)
(use-package :gambol)


